le=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width=
: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background=
-color: #ccc;"> the metaphysics of this</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"mar=
gin: 16px 0;">Russia will halt bond sales for the rest of the year and take=
 legal action if sanctions force it into a default on its debt, according t=
o the country=E2=80=99s finance minister.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A=
nton Siluanov=E2=80=99s comments in Russian newspaper Izvestia come days af=
ter the government breached the terms on two bonds by paying investors rubl=
es instead of dollars, and its credit grade at S&amp;P Global Ratings was c=
ut to =E2=80=98selective default.=E2=80=99</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=
The threat of default has been hanging over Russia for weeks after it was h=
it with sanctions because of its invasion of Ukraine. The government in Mos=
cow says it has the funds to meet its debt obligations and has repeatedly b=
lamed the restrictions for its difficulties in making bond payments. Siluan=
ov has said the U.S. and others are trying to force Russia into default.=C2=
=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9COf course, we will sue, becaus=
e we have taken all the necessary steps to ensure that investors receive th=
eir payments,=E2=80=9D he said, according to Izvestia. =E2=80=9CIt will not=
 be an easy process. We will have to very actively prove our case, despite =
all the difficulties.=E2=80=9D</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"=
>Who will they sue? Where? For what?=C2=A0Russia wants to vindicate the met=
aphysical status of its default as not-really-a-default, but there is not r=
eally a good court for vindicating metaphysical status.</p><p style=3D"marg=
in: 16px 0;">Meanwhile, one problem with doing a fire-sale divestiture of y=
our Russian operations is that you are selling those operations at fire-sal=
e prices <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27330343.=
