</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you spend four years working in a h=
igh-level but informal White House job running Middle East policy, and in t=
hat job you=C2=A0advocate for policies that favor Saudi Arabia, and then yo=
u leave that job and cash in by starting an investment company to be funded=
 largely by the Saudi sovereign wealth fund, is it important for the invest=
ment company to be=C2=A0<em>good</em>? At investing? No, of course not; the=
y are not giving you the money because you are a good investor. It is alway=
s possible that someone at the Saudi sovereign wealth fund will misundersta=
nd, however. The <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/2=
7330343.276596/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubnl0aW1lcy5jb20vMjAyMi8wNC8xMC91cy9qYXJlZC1r=
dXNobmVyLXNhdWRpLWludmVzdG1lbnQtZnVuZC5odG1s/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB8e8ac=
