=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;">New York Times reports</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin:=
 16px 0;">Six months after leaving the White House, Jared Kushner secured a=
 $2 billion investment from a fund led by the Saudi crown prince, a close a=
lly during the Trump administration, despite objections from the fund=E2=80=
=99s advisers about the merits of the deal.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"=
>A panel that screens investments for the main Saudi sovereign wealth fund =
cited concerns about the proposed deal with Mr. Kushner=E2=80=99s newly for=
med private equity firm, Affinity Partners, previously undisclosed document=
s show.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Those objections included: =E2=80=
=9Cthe inexperience of the Affinity Fund management=E2=80=9D; the possibili=
ty that the kingdom would be responsible for =E2=80=9Cthe bulk of the inves=
tment and risk=E2=80=9D; due diligence on the fledgling firm=E2=80=99s oper=
ations that found them =E2=80=9Cunsatisfactory in all aspects=E2=80=9D; a p=
roposed asset management fee that =E2=80=9Cseems excessive=E2=80=9D; and =
=E2=80=9Cpublic relations risks=E2=80=9D from Mr. Kushner=E2=80=99s prior r=
ole as a senior adviser to his father-in-law, former President Donald J. Tr=
ump, according to minutes of the panel=E2=80=99s meeting last June 30.</p><=
/blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But those sorts of misunderstandin=
gs get straightened=C2=A0out between principals:</p><blockquote><p style=3D=
"margin: 16px 0;">But days later the full board of the $620 billion Public =
Investment Fund =E2=80=94 led by Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman, Saudi Ar=
abia=E2=80=99s de facto ruler and a beneficiary of Mr. Kushner=E2=80=99s su=
pport when he worked as a White House adviser =E2=80=94 overruled the panel=
. =E2=80=A6</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Mr. Kushner planned to raise up=
 to $7 billion in all, according to a document prepared last summer for the=
 Saudi fund=E2=80=99s board. But so far he appears to have signed up few ot=
her major investors.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In its most recent pub=
lic filings with the Securities and Exchange Commission, dated March 31, Mr=
. Kushner=E2=80=99s firm reported that its main fund had $2.5 billion under=
 management, almost entirely from investors based overseas. Most of that ap=
pears to be the $2 billion from Saudi Arabia.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"m=
argin: 16px 0;">We <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click=
/27330343.276596/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLz=
IwMTktMDEtMDQvZG9uLXQtY2FsbC1icmliZXMtY2hpY2tlbnM_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDQxMTIyX01PT=
